summary:
Credit card blogs love to recommend buying first class flights abroad to get the most &lsquo;value&rsquo; out of your points, citing 2 to 5 cents per point in some cases.
I think I&rsquo;ve got them beat. Try 9 cents per point for a United Economy flight to Shanghai next April&hellip;
Cash Flights: NYC to Shanghai in April 2022 United Miles Flights NYC to Shanghai in April 2022 The Bonus Rant: It&rsquo;s easy to get caught up in credit card marketing with their crazy miles valuations, sometimes citing the best case with crazy expensive international flight redemptions.
